      "rationale": "All FEA software packages (Ansys Mechanical 2021 R2, FDA in-house solver) operate under documented quality management systems. Version control, regression testing, and release validation records are available. Required gradation 2 is satisfied."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Benchmark problems from ASME V&V 10.1 and vendor verification suites confirm correct implementation of linear elastic and contact formulations. Patch tests passed for all element types employed."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "A systematic mesh convergence study was performed across three refinement levels. The Richardson extrapolation-based grid convergence index (GCI) for construct stiffness was below 2.1% on the finest mesh, confirming discretization error is controlled within acceptable bounds."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
